results.wikipedia_summary: The genus Brachypteryx contains four species known as shortwings. They are colourful medium-sized mostly insectivorous birds. Opinion is divided as to whether they belong in the thrush family Turdidae, or the Old World Flycatcher family Muscicapidae. They show strong sexual plumage dimorphism. All species are southeast Asian.
